Torstol seeds can be planted in a herb patch with level 85 Farming in order to produce grimy torstols. It can be obtained from monsters or as a very rare loot from pickpocketing Master Farmers.

Note: A nearby gardener will not watch over your growing herb.

Picking some torstol from the patch north of East Ardougne is part of the elite Ardougne Diary.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
23 July 2020
(update | poll)

The appearance of herbs planted in herb patches now match the herb's appearance in the player's inventory.

9 January 2020
(update | poll)

Players can now dig up healthy herb patches before they're fully grown. To prevent players from gaining experience by repeatedly planting and digging up herb seeds, the experience usually gained from planting herbs is now given when harvesting them, alongside the usual harvesting experience.

8 February 2018
(update | poll)

The value was changed from 64 to 70 so that it would appear above less valuable seeds when on the ground.

11 July 2005
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Herb seed" to "Torstol seed".
  • The item's examine was changed from "Farming skill coming in July!" to "A torstol seed - plant in a herb patch."
